Text-Associated DeepWalk (TADW) [28] extends DeepWalk to deal with textual attributes. Yang et al. prove, following the work in [17], that Skip-Gram with hierarchical softmax can be equivalently formulated as a matrix factorization problem. TADW then consists in constraining the factorization problem with a pre-computed representation of the documents T by using Latent Semantic Analysis (LSA) [6]. The task is to optimize the objective:1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
