In this paper, we presented IDNE, an inductive document network embedding algorithm that learns word and latent topic representations via TWA, a topic-word attention mechanism able to produce interpretable document representations. We showed that IDNE performs state-of-the-art results on various network in different settings. Moreover, we showed that our attention mechanism provides an efficient way of interpreting the learned representations. In future work, we would like to study the effect of the sampling of the documents on the learned topics. In particular, the matrix \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
